The '''2014–15 European Rugby Champions Cup-Challenge Cup play-off''' was the first play-off for entry into the top level competition of European Club rugby union, the [[European Rugby Champions Cup]].

In March 2014, following the announcement of new European club competitions, the European Rugby Champions Cup and the [[European Rugby Challenge Cup]], it was announced that the final place in the Champions Cup competition would be awarded by a play-off.

For the 2014–15 season, this was a two-legged play-off between the seventh placed teams from the [[2013–14 English Premiership (rugby union)|2013–14 Aviva Premiership]] season, and the [[2013–14 Top 14 season]]. Following the completion of both legs, the team with the highest aggregate score took the twentieth berth in the [[2014–15 European Rugby Champions Cup]], the new top tier competition, while the loser will play in the second tier [[2014–15 European Rugby Challenge Cup]].

